The dual-licensing terms in this file apply to releases v22.10.0 and
later.


==========================================================================
2. NONCOMMERCIAL USE — PolyForm Noncommercial Licence 1.0.0
==========================================================================

For any noncommercial purpose, WolfStack is licensed under the PolyForm
Noncommercial Licence 1.0.0, the full text of which appears as Section 5
below.

The PolyForm Noncommercial Licence permits the following uses without
any payment to Wolf Software Systems Ltd:

  * Personal use on your home network or homelab
  * Education, research, and academic study
  * Charitable, public-good, and non-revenue community projects
  * Evaluation of the Software prior to commercial licensing

The PolyForm Noncommercial Licence does NOT permit the following uses
without a separate commercial licence (see Section 3):

  * Use within or for the benefit of a commercial entity, even for
    purely internal infrastructure
  * Reselling WolfStack, or any service whose value derives from running
    WolfStack
  * Hosting WolfStack as a managed service for third parties
  * Embedding WolfStack into a paid product
  * Any use intended for commercial advantage or monetary compensation


==========================================================================
3. COMMERCIAL USE — Wolf Software Systems Commercial Licence
==========================================================================

Commercial use of WolfStack requires an active subscription to one of
the WolfStack tiers (Homelab, Team, MSP, or Enterprise) issued by Wolf
Software Systems Ltd or an authorised reseller. An active subscription
automatically grants the subscriber a non-exclusive, non-transferable,
worldwide commercial licence to use the Software for any commercial
purpose during the subscription term, including all uses excluded from
the PolyForm Noncommercial Licence in Section 2.

The commercial licence overrides the noncommercial restrictions in
Section 2 with respect to the Subscriber's use of the Software during
the subscription term. The commercial licence:

  * Covers all hosts within the host cap of the subscribed tier (or
    unlimited hosts on tiers that carry no cap)
  * Covers the Subscriber's employees, contractors, and authorised
    agents acting in that capacity
  * Includes the right to make and run modifications privately
  * Includes the right to white-label and resell as a managed service
    on tiers that grant those features (e.g. MSP, Enterprise)
  * Lapses when the subscription lapses or is terminated, after which
    continued commercial use of the affected release requires a new
    subscription or a separate written agreement

To subscribe: https://wolfstack.org/enterprise.php

For terms beyond the standard published tiers — including bespoke SLAs,
on-premises or air-gapped deployment support, audit and compliance
collateral, custom development, or large-fleet pricing — contact
sales@wolf.uk.com to negotiate a separate commercial agreement.


